data.text:
What is band?

What is Vakatagi?

A thin strip of flexible material used to encircle and bind one object or to hold a number of objects together: a metal band around the bale of cotton.

E dua na tiki ni iyaya rawarawa me vakavolivoliti keda ka vauca vata e dua na iyaya se me taura vata e vica na iyaya: e dua na kaukamea kaukamea wavokita na iqi ni vauvau.

A strip or stripe that contrasts with something else in color, texture, or material.

E dua na tiki ni itavoi se itavoi ka veidutaitaka vata kei na dua tale na roka, ituvaki, se iyaya.

A narrow strip of fabric used to trim, finish, or reinforce articles of clothing.

E dua na isulu qiqo me moti, vakaotia, se vaqaqacotaka na veimataqali isulu.

Something that constrains or binds morally or legally: the bands of marriage and family.

E dua na ka e tarova se vauca vakadodonu se vakalawa: na ivau ni vakamau kei na matavuvale.

A simple ungrooved ring, especially a wedding ring.

E dua na mama e sega na kena e vinaka tu, vakabibi e dua na mama ni vakamau.

A neckband or collar.

E dua na iqase se koqa.

The two strips hanging from the front of a collar as part of the dress of certain clerics, scholars, and lawyers.

Erau lili na rua na tiki ni pepa mai na mata ni dua na kote me tiki ni nodra ivinivo eso na vunivola, vuku, kei na loya.

A high collar popular in the 16th and 17th centuries.

E dua na kote levu ka kilai levu ena ika 16 kei na ika 17 ni senitiuri.

Biology A chromatically, structurally, or functionally differentiated strip or stripe in or on an organism.

Na iyaya ni Bula E tuvai vakamatau, vakaituvatuva, se duatani na tiki ni itoqa se kudru ena dua na ituvatuva.

Anatomy A cordlike tissue that connects or holds structures together.

Na isema ni anatomi E dua na isema ka na semati se taura vata na vale.

Physics A specific range of wavelengths or frequencies of electromagnetic radiation.

Fisiki E dua na ivakatagedegede ni ua se na veigauna ni cina me vakayagataki ena ivakatakata ni mavoa -i-a -ni-vuravura.

Physics A range of very closely spaced electron energy levels in solids, the distribution and nature of which determine the electrical properties of a material.

Na Fisiki A vica na itagede ni livaliva e rauta ni maliwa lala ena itagede ni livaliva, na veisoliyaki kei na ituvaki ka vakatulewa kina na gacagaca vakalivaliva ni dua na iyaya.

Any of the distinct grooves on a long-playing phonograph record that contains an individual selection or a separate section of a whole.

Ni dua vei ira na idusidusi duidui ena dua na itukutuku ni vakatagi vakabalavu ka tiko kina e dua na digidigi ni tamata yadua se dua na iwasewase duidui ni dua na iwasewase taucoko.

A cord or strip across the back of a book to which the sheets or quires are attached.

E dua na dali se tikidua ena daku ni dua na ivola ka vesu tu kina na siti se na iqaqi ni vale.

To tie, bind, or encircle with or as if with a band.

Me vesuki, vauci, se vakavolivoliti iko se me vaka e dua na ilawalawa.

To mark or identify with or as if with a band: a program to band migrating birds.

Me makataki se kilai se me vaka e dua na ilawalawa: e dua na parokaramu me vakatagitaki ira na manumanu vuka.

A group of people: a band of outlaws.

E dua na ilawalawa tamata: e dua na ilawalawa tawasei.

A group of animals.

E dua na ilawalawa manumanu.

Anthropology A unit of social organization especially among hunter-gatherers, consisting of a usually small number of families living together cooperatively.

Na isoqosoqo vakatamata e dua na isoqosoqo raraba vakabibi vei ira era dau vakasoqoni ira vata na dauvakasasa, ka ra dau lewe lailai ga kina na matavuvale era bula vata tiko.

Canadian An aboriginal group officially recognized as an organized unit by the Canadian government. See Usage Note at First Nation.

E dua na ilawalawa ka a tauyavutaki e Kenada e dua na tabanilotu ka tauyavutaki mai na matanitu o Kenada. Raica na iDusidusi ni Kena Vakayagataki ena iMatai ni Matanitu.

A group of musicians who perform as an ensemble.

E dua na ilawalawa ni daunivakatagi era dau lagasere vata vakailawalawa.

To assemble or unite in a group.

Me vakasoqoni vata se duavata ena dua na ilawalawa.
